text: OK, everyone.
Let's get weird.

(SINGING) I may be odd, but
that's OK 'cause everyone
is unique in their own way.

My little bro does
not wear shoes.
This quirky girl became a witch.
Her name is Luz.
Libby writes poetry.
Doof loves his enemy.

Kiff's going to do the worm
and tear up the dance floor.
Don't dwell on what's allowed.
You go, girl, Penny Proud.

Moon Girl is fighting
crime beside a dinosaur.
'Cause we were born to be strange.

The world is way more fun
marching to your own drum.
No need to change.

Quick, Scratch
should not be feared.
Gotta embrace the weird.
Eda's a rebel.
She's breaking the law.
Gramma is a fighter.
Who cares if she's old?

Scrooge is a weirdo
who swims in his gold.
Yes, we were born to be strange.

Mabel will spend all day
just working on crochet.

Hamsters that fly and
witches that walk,

teddy bear robots and
food that can talk,

gamers, campaigners,
and royals named star.

Don't be afraid to
be who you are 'cause
we were born to be strange.

Life is more interesting
when you do your own thing.
No need to change.

Glomgold going to spend all
night scheming with dynamite.

Even if you have two giant feet
that doesn't mean you can't

keep a beat or win the
day by just being sweet

'cause we were
born to be strange.

We're never gonna hid
how weird we are inside.
Well, that was weird.
Oh.
Thank you, Saxon.
